### Usage

How to enable the page excerpt manually:

~~~ .yaml
---
title: Page Title
description: Page description.
author: Taufik Nurrohman
type: Markdown
...

This paragraph is going to be the page excerpt.

&#12;

Rest of the page content goes here.
~~~

You can also use `&#xC;` to limit the manual page excerpt length.

To show the manual page excerpt in your layout:

~~~ .html
<?php foreach ($pages as $page): ?>
  <article>
    <h3>
      <?= $page->title; ?>
    </h3>
    <?= $page->excerpt; ?>
    <p>
      <a href="<?= $page->url; ?>#next:<?= $page->id; ?>">
        <?= i('Read More'); ?>
      </a>
    </p>
  </article>
<?php endforeach; ?>
~~~

By default, this extension will not insert any HTML markup as the jump target. Excerpt marker will be normalized into native form feed character in the output. You can add a hook in your layoutâ€™s `index.php` file to convert the character into HTML markup to jump to:

~~~ .php
Hook::set('page.content', function($content) {
    return strtr($content, ["\f" => '<span id="next:' . $this->id . '" role="doc-pagebreak"></span>']);
});
~~~

You may need to add this CSS code to make the jump stop more precise:

~~~ .css
[role='doc-pagebreak'] {
  display: block;
}
~~~